{
  "texts": [
    "These adaptive test models evolve with the software, ensuring that the most relevant and risky areas are continuously validated.",
    "c. Machine Learning for Predictive Test Case Prioritization Supervised learning models, such as random forests and support vector machines, have been trained on defect logs and code metrics to predict which test cases are more likely to uncover bugs.",
    "This predictive prioritization helps optimize regression testing by focusing on the most failure-prone scenarios, thereby saving time and improving quality.",
    "Feature inputs often include cyclomatic complexity, churn rates, code ownership, and prior bug density.",
    "Test data is essential for validating software behavior under various input conditions."
  ]
}